20you%20as%20an%20artisan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20when%20I%20was%2026%2C%20in%20my%20second%20job%20after%20graduating%20from%20the%20Nanyang%20Academy%20of%20Fine%20Arts%20in%20Singapore%20with%20a%20diploma%20in%20fashion%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20job%20was%20with%20an%20independent%20tailor%2C%20where%20I%20worked%20for%20one-and-a-half%20years.%20Then%2C%20a%20friend%20working%20at%20Goyard's%20then-distributor%20in%20Singapore%20approached%20me%20as%20they%20were%20bringing%20in%20the%20brand%20and%20needed%20a%20customization%20artist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20sent%20me%20to%20Carcassonne%2C%20in%20the%20south%20of%20France%2C%20for%20about%20two%20weeks%20of%20training%20in%202013.%20I%20painted%20on%20the%20brand's%20canvas%2C%20just%20like%20what%20clients%20would%20request%20for%20their%20customizations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20really%20happy%20with%20my%20work%2C%20so%20I%20passed%20the%20assessment%20and%20came%20back%20to%20Singapore%20to%20start%20the%20customization%20studio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20day%2C%20I%20painted%20what%20clients%20wanted%20on%20their%20bags.%20The%20standard%20requests%20were%20initials%20and%20stripes%2C%20but%20there%20were%20also%20portraits%20and%20pets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224128%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jasline%20Ang%20when%20she%20was%20an%20artist%20at%20Goyard.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c9667af9db348adc0b898c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222322%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJasline%20Ang's%20first%20job%20was%20with%20Goyard%2C%20where%20she%20set%20up%20the%20brand's%20first%20customization%20in%20Singapore.%3Cp%3EJasline%20Ang%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20years%20taught%20me%20about%20luxury%2C%20craftsmanship%2C%20quality%2C%20and%20precision.%20We're%20trained%20to%20be%20really%20careful%3B%20if%20we%20make%20a%20major%20mistake%2C%20the%20bag%20is%20done.%20I%20think%20it%20happened%20to%20one%20or%20two%20bags.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20artist%2C%20I%20was%20very%20lucky%20to%20get%20a%20good%2C%20steady%20paycheck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20about%20four%20years%2C%20I%20felt%20ready%20to%20make%20a%20move.%20There%20was%20an%20opening%20at%20Louis%20Vuitton%2C%20so%20I%20joined%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Louis%20Vuitton%2C%20the%20painting%20is%20done%20in-store%20and%20only%20on%20the%20hard-sided%20pieces%2C%20like%20the%20big%20trunks.%20It%20felt%20more%20freestyle%20and%20artistic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222961%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jasline%20Ang%20at%20work%20at%20Louis%20Vuitton.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c966a9183847aa39d6d662%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223948%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJasline%20Ang%20spent%20over%20four%20years%20as%20an%20inhouse%20customization%20artist%20at%20Louis%20Vuitton.%3Cp%3EJasline%20Ang%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20working%20on%20a%20feng%20shui%20series%20across%20five%20hat%20boxes%2C%20including%20a%20dragon%20on%20one%20and%20a%20phoenix%20on%20another.%20Then%2C%20there%20was%20a%20big%20leopard%20that%20I%20painted%20across%20a%20stack%20of%20trunks%2C%20so%20the%20image%20connected%20when%20you%20stacked%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20always%20something%20big%20and%20exciting%20for%20big%20brands%3A%20a%20party%2C%20a%20show%2C%20and%20travel%20around%20the%20Southeast%20Asia%20and%20Australia%20region.%20The%20benefits%20were%20good%2C%20and%20business%20was%20booming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20a%20while%2C%20I%20felt%20creative%20stagnation.%20Since%20you're%20always%20executing%20whatever%20the%20client%20wants%2C%20you%20can't%20really%20have%20your%20own%20particular%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20quit%20in%202022%2C%20freelanced%2C%20and%20then%20started%20my%20own%20business%20about%20a%20year%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2245c75435-6868-4ed4-89dd-cb1cdd6db98f%5C%22%3ELeaping%20from%20luxury%20to%20my%20own%20studio%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20something%20unique%20and%20scalable%20%E2%80%94%20and%20with%20room%20for%20me%20to%20express%20creatively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20brainstormed%20with%20my%20close%20friend%20Melissa%20Tan.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20she%20didn't%20want%20to%20continue%20her%20corporate%20HR%20job%20at%20Loewe%2C%20too%2C%20so%20we%20started%20this%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20wanted%20a%20strong%20identity%20that's%20recognizable%20and%20niche%20enough%20that%20we%20don't%20have%20to%20compete%20so%20hard.%20Fashion%20and%20hand-drawn%20prints%20married%20my%20two%20greatest%20strengths.%20After%20years%20in%20luxury%2C%20this%20combination%20just%20made%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20named%20the%20studio%20Qiling%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BQi%26quot%3B%20is%20her%20Chinese%20name%2C%20and%20%26quot%3BLing%26quot%3B%20is%20mine.%20Qiling%20is%20also%20the%20name%20of%20a%20mythical%20creature%20in%20Chinese%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20with%20Melissa%20is%20really%20the%20best%20combination.%20At%20Studio%20Qiling%2C%20I%20handle%20the%20creative%20day-to-day%2C%20and%20Melissa%20runs%20operations%20and%20finance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Studio%20Qiling%20cofounders%20Jasline%20Ang%20and%20Melissa%20Tan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c966f3f9db348adc0b899b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJasline%20Ang%20set%20up%20Studio%20Qiling%20with%20her%20longtime%20friend%20Melissa%20Tan%20in%202023.%3Cp%3EJasline%20Ang%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20used%20our%20own%20savings%20and%20still%20do%20nearly%20everything%20ourselves.%20For%20our%20first%20products%2C%20we%20launched%20small%2C%20limited%20runs%20of%20items%20at%20a%20design%20fair%2C%20and%20the%20response%20was%20better%20than%20we%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECustomers%20really%20loved%20my%20designs%20and%20original%20prints%20on%20silk%20scarves%20with%20hand-rolled%20edges%2C%20kimonos%2C%20and%20pareos.%20My%20prints%20are%20inspired%20by%20nature%20and%20come%20with%20a%20whimsical%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20small%20brand%2C%20we%20can%20keep%20prices%20competitive%20while%20using%20the%20best%20quality%20and%20materials.%20We%20produce%20in%20small%20quantities%20and%20do%20not%20offer%20discounts.%20I%20design%20pieces%20to%20be%20timeless%20so%20customers%20can%20wear%20them%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERunning%20a%20boutique%20label%20in%20Singapore%20is%20expensive.%20The%20market%20is%20small%2C%20competition%20is%20global%2C%20and%20expectations%20are%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20now%20profitable%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20still%20isn't%20%E2%80%94%20easy.%20We%20did%20not%20pay%20ourselves%20salaries%20for%20the%20first%20year%2C%20and%20I'm%20definitely%20drawing%20less%20than%20what%20I%20used%20to%20make%20at%20Louis%20Vuitton.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2231728ffa-91d4-49ed-b62f-24dfb8d2ce0d%5C%22%3EDreaming%20bigger%20with%20AI%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20artist%2C%20I%20really%20enjoy%20what%20AI%20has%20to%20offer.%20Some%20artists%20say%20AI%20is%20taking%20over%20our%20jobs%2C%20but%20I'm%20not%20in%20that%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20use%20ChatGPT%20and%20Midjourney%20to%20create%20campaign%20visuals%20you%20can%20see%20on%20our%20Instagram.%20I'll%20direct%20AI%20to%20render%20the%20model%20and%20the%20scene%20%E2%80%94%20like%20a%20lotus%2C%20or%20something%20mythical%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20I%20create%20a%20composite%20with%20real%20photos%20of%20our%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20create%20a%20shoot%20like%20that%20in%20real%20life%20would%20be%20very%20costly.%20With%20AI%2C%20I%20can%20achieve%20the%20mood%20I%20want.%20It%20takes%20about%20one%20full%20day%2C%20but%20it%20expands%20the%20possibilities%20for%20our%20marketing%20campaigns%20and%20allows%20us%20to%20experiment.%3C%2Fp%3E